Dear Colleagues,

This is the second announcement for a Summer School on selected topics =
in category theory and in algebraic topology, which will take place at =
the EPFL in Lausanne, Switzerland from Thursday 11 to Saturday 13 =
September 2014. There will be three mini-courses of 4 1/2 hours each.

Marino Gran (UCL):  Semi-abelian categories, semi-localizations, and =
torsion theories

J=E9r=F4me Scherer (EPFL):  About localization and cellularization

Enrico Vitale (UCL):  Categorical groups:  a bit of theory and some =
applications to homological and homotopical algebra

Please see the webpage of the conference at the address =
http://sites.uclouvain.be/ctat2014/ for more details.

There is no conference fee to attend the Summer School; however, =
registration is required.

In order to register, please send an email with your affiliation to =
kathryn.hess@epfl.ch by June 30, 2014.=20

At the beginning of July documents concerning the prerequisites for the =
mini-courses will be made available to the registered participants.

We look forward to seeing you in Lausanne!

Best wishes,

Kathryn Hess and Marino Gran


[For admin and other information see: http://www.mta.ca/~cat-dist/ ]

